The paper deals with the problem of self-assembly of discrete Sierpinski triangles, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The Tile Assembly Model is a computational model that falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of DNA tiles and atomic-force microscopy suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the use of optimal counters and corner-turning operations, which are topics in discrete structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT).
